Do a global search for the hexadecimal number 57 (W) in a string:

Copy
let str = "Visit Demo2s.com. Hello World!";
let patt1 = /\x57/g;
let result = str.match(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The \xdd character can find the Latin character specified by a hexadecimal number dd.

If no match is found, it returns null.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
\xdd	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("\\xdd") or simply: /\xdd/
Syntax with modifiers
Copy
new RegExp("\\xdd", "g") or simply: /\xdd/g
